p: The regression model did not reveal an effect of the virus serotype on the infection rates of Ae. aegypti populations ( Table 5). However, odds ratio of mosquito strain from Saint-Louis versus mosquito strains from Dakar, decreases significantly by a factor of 0.4 (p<0.001) while relative proportion of infected mosquitoes increases by a factor of 3.5 at 15 dpbm compared to 7 dpbm (p<0.001).
